{
  "text": "In the statistical physics of spin glasses the equations presented in this section are called the replica symmetric cavity equations. A large amount of work has been devoted to understanding under what circumstances these equations give asymptotically exact results for the marginals and the free energy, and when they do not [4, [CITATION_1] . All known cases when the replica symmetric solution of a model like (8) is not correct on a randomly generated network can be divided into two classes: a static spin glass phase with spin glass susceptibility",
